# Unit Test Isolation

- Unit tests must not verify behavior by accessing the real filesystem.
- Do not read or write real device paths (for example `/dev/input/*`) in unit tests.
- Prefer pure-function tests, test doubles, and in-memory test data.
- If filesystem behavior must be validated, use integration tests instead of unit tests.

